class="t m879 xbd h2f y5d9 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">STUDY HELP: &quot;Patriarchs and Prophets,&quot; pp. 44-51, 111-116. </div><div class="t me02 xf h87 y4ef ff1 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Creation the Direct Act of God </div><div class="t m48b x16 h1 ycf9 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m32d x48 h1 ycf9 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How do the Scriptures account for this earth&apos;s existence? Gen. </div><div class="t m8d5 xbd h1 y75 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1:1; John 1:1-3, 14; Heb. 1:2. </div><div class="t m56 x16 he y164 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nom.—Repeatedly Bible writers ascribe creation to an act of God. To </div><div class="t maf7 x4 he yf60 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">deny this truth does not merely involve the rejection of Genesis, chapters one </div><div class="t m77e xbd he y1474 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and two, but a denial of the entire Bible and of its Author. </div><div class="t mae7 x16 h1 y42c ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m22e x48 h1 y42c ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What Bible statements tell how the world was created? Heb. </div><div class="t m119e x4 h1 y411 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11:3; Ps. 33:6, 9. </div><div class="t m1068 x16 h2f y716 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—We </div><div class="t m40b x3f he y4c7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">know from the record in Genesis that there were stages </div><div class="t m1938 xdc h1 y4c7 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in </div><div class="t m115f xdb he y4c7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the </div><div class="t m3f0 x4 he yc9 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">process of creation day by day, and the Bible is equally clear that the material </div><div class="t m2fa x4 he y1c3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">out of which the world was formed was spoken into existence by God. </div><div class="t m308 x71 h1 y882 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m6b9 x48 h1 y882 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How long was God in creating the heaven and the earth? Ex. </div><div class="t m2437 xbd h1 y448 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws